My cousin posted her adoption anniversary today. Here’s a picture of me and the judge the day I was adopted. I think this was spring 2000 idk 😅 That’s my Big sister to the Right, and my Big and little cousin towards the left-ish lol. 

We had a little cake to celebrate.. I was so confused I’m not going to lie. Everything happened so quick. I became the second Child of (7) from my mother that got adopted. ￼

My mom or my dad wasn’t there, but idk if that was purposely or not. little do people know or WANT to believe is that I don’t really remember much of my mother. ￼I know her absence wasn’t purposely. ￼She was a human being, and LIFE be LIFEING, she probably was so scattered brained daily and in pain I pray she’s at peace, GOD rest her soul and simmer her pain.

I feel bad for her because sometimes parents usually get it together by the time they have their youngest child, so I wonder if she felt defeated because yet again another one of her children got adopted… and then I was her youngest, Sigh… 😓 

I’m very greatful to be adopted because originally I was in foster care in the veeeeryyy beginning LOL imagine being snatched from your biological mother arms￼, and then grabbed from your foster mothers arms and then snatched your grandmothers arms…. All as a baby. I yi yi The journey it’s been… Rest In peace to my Mother and my Grandmother. And S/O to my Aunt Peachie and Aunt Rah Rah.🕊️ Everything wasn’t perfect, but we’re not ROBOTS we’re HUMAN BEINGS. 

In my family 

Our Aunts are also our mothers
Our Cousins are also our siblings
So on and so fourth…

People say I don’t share much, so here’s a LITTLE bit. ￼I’m sure In The Future I’ll write a book…. I guess the next chapter after this would be alopecia, because shortly after I was adopted  then Alopecia made its appearance. ￼Whew 😮‍💨
